<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-59-0255 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper presents the results of an experiment dealing with the absorptionof electromagnetic waves in a longitudinally magnetized plasma waveguideat electron cyclotron frequency. Our results demonstrate, under differentoperating conditions, the importance of the polarization of the incidentwaves as well as the linear behavior of the plasma density as a functionof the absorbed power. The gas used in this study was argon.</TEXT></DOC>